terminology.cryptitis: inflammation of the crypts of lieberkühn and is seen in both crohn’s disease and ulcerative colitis
terminology.dysplasia: abnormal epithelial growth and is associated with precancerous changes, often seen in long-standing ulcerative colitis or crohn’s disease

terminology.cryptitis: inflammation of the crypts, characterized by infiltration of neutrophils into the crypt epithelium
terminology.dysplasia: abnormal growth and differentiation of epithelial cells, often seen in precancerous lesions

terminology.cryptitis: inflammation of the intestinal crypts, characterized by neutrophilic infiltration into the crypt epithelium
terminology.dysplasia: precancerous changes in the epithelium, often seen in long-standing inflammatory bowel disease as a precursor to colorectal cancer
